		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Scientific visualization</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:282px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Instability.jpg" class="image" title="A scientific visualization of an extremely large simulation of a Raleigh-Taylor instability caused by two mixing fluids.[1]"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/17/Instability.jpg/280px-Instability.jpg" width="280" height="280" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Instability.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A scientific visualization of an extremely large simulation of a Raleigh-Taylor instability caused by two mixing fluids.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Scientific visualization</b> (<a href="/wiki/Ise_vs_ize" title="Ise vs ize" class="mw-redirect">also spelled</a> <b>scientific visualisation</b>) is an <a href="/wiki/Interdisciplinary" title="Interdisciplinary" class="mw-redirect">interdisciplinary</a> branch of science, primarily concerned with the <a href="/wiki/Visualization" title="Visualization">visualization</a> of <a href="/wiki/Three-dimensional_space" title="Three-dimensional space">three dimensional</a> phenomena, such as architectural, meteorological, medical, biological systems. The emphasis is on realistic <a href="/wiki/Rendering" title="Rendering" class="mw-redirect">rendering</a> of volumes, surfaces, illumination sources, and so forth, perhaps with a dynamic (time) component.<sup id="cite_ref-MF08_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-MF08-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Scientific visualization focuses on the use of <a href="/wiki/Computer_graphics" title="Computer graphics">computer graphics</a> to create visual <a href="/wiki/Images" title="Images" class="mw-redirect">images</a> which aid in understanding of complex, often massive numerical representation of scientific concepts or results.<sup id="cite_ref-BHM94_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BHM94-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
